
Preheat oven to 350 F.

Beat 5 oz melted butter and 1 c granulated sugar. Add 2 eggs, 2 tsp vanilla, 4
oz melted chocolate, 1/4 c cocoa, and 1/2 c milk and mix well. Mix in 2 c + 2
tbsp flour, 1 1/2 tsp baking powder, and 1 c chopped candied ginger. 

Shape into 1" balls and roll in confectioner's sugar. Bake for 10-12 minutes. 
Makes about 50 cookies. 


Ingredients: 
5 oz butter, melted
1 c granulated sugar
2 eggs
2 tsp vanilla
4 oz bittersweet chocolate, melted
1/4 c cocoa powder
1/2 c milk
2 c + 2 tbsp white flour
1 1/2 tsp baking powder
1 c chopped candied ginger
Confectioner's sugar
